portFunction.name: portFunction
portFunction.description: Specifies the behavior of the HWC physical ports.

portEnabled.name: portEnabled
portEnabled.description: If enabled, the interface administratively is enabled.

portName.name: portName
portName.description: A textual string containing information about the port.

portIpAddress.name: portIpAddress
portIpAddress.description: The IP address of this port.

portMask.name: portMask
portMask.description: The subnet mask associated with the IP address of this port.

portVlanID.name: portVlanID
portVlanID.description: External VLAN tag for the physical port for trasmitted and received packets. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

portDHCPEnable.name: portDHCPEnable
portDHCPEnable.description: If enabled, the controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPGateway.name: portDHCPGateway
portDHCPGateway.description: Gateway address to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDomain.name: portDHCPDomain
portDHCPDomain.description: Domain name to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDefaultLease.name: portDHCPDefaultLease
portDHCPDefaultLease.description: Default DHCP lease time in seconds to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPMaxLease.name: portDHCPMaxLease
portDHCPMaxLease.description: Maximum DHCP lease time in seconds to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPDnsServers.name: portDHCPDnsServers
portDHCPDnsServers.description: List of DNSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

portDHCPWins.name: portDHCPWins
portDHCPWins.description: List of WINSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if controller is configured as default DHCP server for AP.

physicalPortsInternalVlanID.name: physicalPortsInternalVlanID
physicalPortsInternalVlanID.description: Internal VLAN tag to be used for physical ports for which the exernal VLAN tag have not been configured. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

phyDHCPRangeTable.name: phyDHCPRangeTable
phyDHCPRangeTable.description: phyDHCPRangeTable contains the IP address ranges that DHCP will serve to clients associated with physical ports.

phyDHCPRangeEntry.name: phyDHCPRangeEntry
phyDHCPRangeEntry.description: Configuration information for a DHCP range.

phyDHCPRangeIndex.name: phyDHCPRangeIndex
phyDHCPRangeIndex.description: Index for the DHCP row element.

phyDHCPRangeStart.name: phyDHCPRangeStart
phyDHCPRangeStart.description: First IP address in the range.

phyDHCPRangeEnd.name: phyDHCPRangeEnd
phyDHCPRangeEnd.description: Last IP address in the range.

phyDHCPRangeType.name: phyDHCPRangeType
phyDHCPRangeType.description: Determines whether addresses in the specified range will be included, or excluded by the DHCP server.

phyDHCPRangeStatus.name: phyDHCPRangeStatus
phyDHCPRangeStatus.description: Row status variable for row operations on the phyDHCPRangeTable

vnRole.name: vnRole
vnRole.description: Specifies the role of this HWC in inter-HWC mobility. None indicates that mobile units cannot roam to or from this HWC. In any HWC cluster, only one HWC should be specified as vnMgr, all others should be have vnRole = vnAgent.

vnIfIndex.name: vnIfIndex
vnIfIndex.description: ifIndex of the physical port where inter-HWC tunnels terminate. This field has meaning if vnRole is not none(1)

vnHeartbeatInterval.name: vnHeartbeatInterval
vnHeartbeatInterval.description: The time interval between inter-HWC polling messages. This field has meaning if vnRole is not none(1)

ntpEnabled.name: ntpEnabled
ntpEnabled.description: Enable or disables support for the Network Time Protocol (NTP).

ntpTimezone.name: ntpTimezone
ntpTimezone.description: Specifies the time zone where this HWC resides.

ntpServerEnabled.name: ntpServerEnabled
ntpServerEnabled.description: Enable or disables support for controller as NTP server.

tunnelCount.name: tunnelCount
tunnelCount.description: Number of connections to other WirelessController controllers.

tunnelStatsTable.name: tunnelStatsTable
tunnelStatsTable.description: tunnelStatsTable contains a list of the IP tunnels connected to this HWC for use in inter-HWC mobility.

tunnelStartIP.name: tunnelStartIP
tunnelStartIP.description: IP address for the start of the tunnel.

tunnelStartHWC.name: tunnelStartHWC
tunnelStartHWC.description: Name of the access controller for the start of the tunnel.

tunnelEndIP.name: tunnelEndIP
tunnelEndIP.description: IP address for the end of the tunnel.

tunnelEndHWC.name: tunnelEndHWC
tunnelEndHWC.description: Name of the access controller for the end of the tunnel.

tunnelStatus.name: tunnelStatus
tunnelStatus.description: Indicates if the mobility tunnel is up or down.

vnsCount.name: vnsCount
vnsCount.description: Number of VNSes defined in vnsConfigTable.

vnsConfigTable.name: vnsConfigTable
vnsConfigTable.description: Contains definitions of the Virtual Network Segments defined on this WirelessController.

vnsConfigEntry.name: vnsConfigEntry
vnsConfigEntry.description: Configuration elements for a specific Virtual Network Segment.

vnsAssignmentMode.name: vnsAssignmentMode
vnsAssignmentMode.description: Determines the method by which mobile units are assigned an address within this VNS. If vnsAssignmentMode = ssid, any client with an SSID matching the VNS will be assigned an address from this VNS. If vnsAssignmentMode == aaa, then address assignment is not completed until after the user is authenticated.

vnsMUSessionTimeout.name: vnsMUSessionTimeout
vnsMUSessionTimeout.description: Client session idle time out, in seconds.

vnsAllowMulticast.name: vnsAllowMulticast
vnsAllowMulticast.description: When true, allows IP multicast packets to be broadcast to the clients on this VNS.

vnsSSID.name: vnsSSID
vnsSSID.description: Service Set Identifier (i.e. Network Name) that will be configured on the AccessPoints associated with this VNS.

vnsDomain.name: vnsDomain
vnsDomain.description: Domain name to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsDNSServers.name: vnsDNSServers
vnsDNSServers.description: List of DNSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsWINSServers.name: vnsWINSServers
vnsWINSServers.description: List of WINSs to be supplied to the wireless clients if internal DHCP address assignment.

vnsAuthModel.name: vnsAuthModel
vnsAuthModel.description: vnsAuthModel specifies the authentication method used for clients in the VNS. None indicates that the VNS is open, and no authentication is required. vnsAuthModel=captivePortal may only be specified for a VNS with vnsAssignmentMode=ssid. Likewise, vnsAuthModel=dot1X may only be specified for a VNS with vnsAssignmentMode=aaa.

vnsParentIfIndex.name: vnsParentIfIndex
vnsParentIfIndex.description: Specifies the ifIndex of the parent VNS, if this VNS is a child. If this is a top level VNS, vnsParentIfIndex will return null or 0.

vnsMgmtTrafficEnable.name: vnsMgmtTrafficEnable
vnsMgmtTrafficEnable.description: Specifies whether clients in the VNS have access to HWC management elements.

vnsUseDHCPRelay.name: vnsUseDHCPRelay
vnsUseDHCPRelay.description: This variable indicates what type of DHCP is used for the VNS. none(0): No DHCP server on the VNS. dhcpRelay(1): Uses DHCP relay to reach the DHCP server. localDhcp(2): Uses local DHCP server on the controler.

vns3rdPartyAP.name: vns3rdPartyAP
vns3rdPartyAP.description: When true, specifies that the VNS contains 3rd party access points. Only one such VNS may be defined for a WirelessController.

vnsStatus.name: vnsStatus
vnsStatus.description: RowStatus variable for performing row operations on vnsConfigTable.

vnsMode.name: vnsMode
vnsMode.description: Type of traffic for this VNS. routed(1): The traffic is routed at the controller. bridgeAtController(2): Traffic is bridged at controller. bridgeAtAP(3): Traffic is bridged at Access Points. wds(4): Wireless Distributed System (WDS) type of VNS. If VNS is type of wds(4), then only vnsSupressSSID, vnsDescription and vnsSSID has meaning.

vnsVlanID.name: vnsVlanID
vnsVlanID.description: VLAN tag for the packets trasmitted to/from of the VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2) or bridgeAtAP(3). If vnsMode = bridgeAtController(2), tagging is done at controller. If vnsMode = bridgeAtAP(3), tagging is done at Access Point. Value ranges: (-1) it is not tagged, zero(0) means reserved, 1-4094 tag value.

vnsInterfaceName.name: vnsInterfaceName
vnsInterfaceName.description: Physical interface to be used in the controller for trasmitting/receiving packets for the VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2).

vnsMgmIpAddress.name: vnsMgmIpAddress
vnsMgmIpAddress.description: IP address of the management port associated to this VNS. This value has meaning if vnsMode is bridgeAtController(2).

vnsSuppressSSID.name: vnsSuppressSSID
vnsSuppressSSID.description: If set to true, this prevents this SSID from appearing in the beacon message.

vnsApplyPowerBackOff.name: vnsApplyPowerBackOff
vnsApplyPowerBackOff.description: Indicates whether the AP will direct 802.11h-enabled clients to apply the same power back-off setting that the AP is using

vnsProcessClientIEReq.name: vnsProcessClientIEReq
vnsProcessClientIEReq.description: If true, enables support for 802.11d client information request.

vnsDLSSupportEnable.name: vnsDLSSupportEnable
vnsDLSSupportEnable.description: If true, enables support for DLS Support. This value has meaning only if vnsUseDHCPRelay is selected as localDhcp(2) and vnsMode is select as either routed(1) or bridgeAtController(2).

vnsDLSAddress.name: vnsDLSAddress
vnsDLSAddress.description: DNS IP Address for DLS associated to this VNS. It could be IP address or Name

vnsDLSPort.name: vnsDLSPort
vnsDLSPort.description: DNS Port for DLS associated to this VNS.

vnsRateControlProfile.name: vnsRateControlProfile
vnsRateControlProfile.description: The Rate Control Profile that is referenced by this VNS.

vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable.name: vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable
vnsSessionAvailabilityEnable.description: To indicate if Session Availability feature is enabled.

vnsDHCPRangeTable.name: vnsDHCPRangeTable
vnsDHCPRangeTable.description: vnsDHCPRangeTable contains the IP address ranges that DHCP will serve to clients associated with this VNS.

vnsDHCPRangeEntry.name: vnsDHCPRangeEntry
vnsDHCPRangeEntry.description: Configuration information for a DHCP range.

vnsDHCPRangeIndex.name: vnsDHCPRangeIndex
vnsDHCPRangeIndex.description: Index for the DHCP row element.

vnsDHCPRangeStart.name: vnsDHCPRangeStart
vnsDHCPRangeStart.description: First IP address in the range.

vnsDHCPRangeEnd.name: vnsDHCPRangeEnd
vnsDHCPRangeEnd.description: Last IP address in the range.

vnsDHCPRangeType.name: vnsDHCPRangeType
vnsDHCPRangeType.description: Determines whether addresses in the specified range will be included, or excluded by the DHCP server.

vnsDHCPRangeStatus.name: vnsDHCPRangeStatus
vnsDHCPRangeStatus.description: Row status variable for row operations on the vnsDHCPRangeTable

vnsCaptivePortalTable.name: vnsCaptivePortalTable
vnsCaptivePortalTable.description: Details of the Captive Portal login page for VNSes that have vnsAssignment=ssid and vnsAuthModel=captivePortal.

vnsCaptivePortalEntry.name: vnsCaptivePortalEntry
vnsCaptivePortalEntry.description: Captive Portal Information for the VNS.

cpURL.name: cpURL
cpURL.description: Redirect URL of the Captive Portal login page.

cpLoginLabel.name: cpLoginLabel
cpLoginLabel.description: Label that appears in front of the login field on the Captive Portal login page.

cpPasswordLabel.name: cpPasswordLabel
cpPasswordLabel.description: Label that appears in front of the password field on the Captive Portal login page.

cpHeaderURL.name: cpHeaderURL
cpHeaderURL.description: URL of the Captive Portal header.

cpFooterURL.name: cpFooterURL
cpFooterURL.description: URL of the Captive Portal footer.

cpMessage.name: cpMessage
cpMessage.description: A welcome message, or set of instructions that is to appear on the Captive Portal login page.

cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN.name: cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN
cpReplaceGatewayWithFQDN.description: Fully Qualified Domain Name (FQDN) to be used as the gateway IP address.

cpDefaultRedirectionURL.name: cpDefaultRedirectionURL
cpDefaultRedirectionURL.description: Default Redirect URL of the Captive Portal login page.

cpConnectionIP.name: cpConnectionIP
cpConnectionIP.description: IP address of the Controller interface for Captive Portal.

cpConnectionPort.name: cpConnectionPort
cpConnectionPort.description: Port number on the cpConnectionIP interface.

cpSharedSecret.name: cpSharedSecret
cpSharedSecret.description: Secret Key to be used to encrypt the information passed between the Controller and the external web server. It is the password common to both Controller and the external web server.

cpLogOff.name: cpLogOff
cpLogOff.description: Toggles the display of logoff popup screen, allowing users to control their logoff.

cpStatusCheck.name: cpStatusCheck
cpStatusCheck.description: Toggles the display of popup window with session statistics for users to monitor their usage and time left in session.

cpType.name: cpType
cpType.description: Type of captive portal is enabled for the selected VNS.

vnsRadiusServerTable.name: vnsRadiusServerTable
vnsRadiusServerTable.description: List of RADIUS servers to be utilized for authentication in the VNS.

vnsRadiusServerEntry.name: vnsRadiusServerEntry
vnsRadiusServerEntry.description: Configuration information for a RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerPort.name: vnsRadiusServerPort
vnsRadiusServerPort.description: Port number for the RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerRetries.name: vnsRadiusServerRetries
vnsRadiusServerRetries.description: Number of retries for a RADIUS authentication request.

vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret.name: vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret
vnsRadiusServerSharedSecret.description: Shared secret to be used between the NAS and RADIUS server.

vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier.name: vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier
vnsRadiusServerNASIdentifier.description: NAS identifier to be included in RADIUS request.

vnsRadiusServerNasAddress.name: vnsRadiusServerNasAddress
vnsRadiusServerNasAddress.description: NAS address to be included in RADIUS request.

vnsFilterIDTable.name: vnsFilterIDTable
vnsFilterIDTable.description: Table of names filters for a VNS.

vnsFilterIDEntry.name: vnsFilterIDEntry
vnsFilterIDEntry.description: Name of a specific filter in the VNS.

vnsFilterRuleTable.name: vnsFilterRuleTable
vnsFilterRuleTable.description: Table containing specific filters for a named filter.

vnsFilterRuleEntry.name: vnsFilterRuleEntry
vnsFilterRuleEntry.description: Filter elements for an individual VNS filter.

vnsFilterRuleOrder.name: vnsFilterRuleOrder
vnsFilterRuleOrder.description: Position of the filter in the filter list.

vnsFilterRuleDirection.name: vnsFilterRuleDirection
vnsFilterRuleDirection.description: Traffic direction to apply the rule.

vnsFilterRuleAction.name: vnsFilterRuleAction
vnsFilterRuleAction.description: Allow or deny traffic for the filter.

vnsFilterRuleIPAddress.name: vnsFilterRuleIPAddress
vnsFilterRuleIPAddress.description: IP address to apply the filter.

vnsFilterRulePortLow.name: vnsFilterRulePortLow
vnsFilterRulePortLow.description: Low port number for the filter.

vnsFilterRulePortHigh.name: vnsFilterRulePortHigh
vnsFilterRulePortHigh.description: High port number for the filter.

vnsPrivacyTable.name: vnsPrivacyTable
vnsPrivacyTable.description: Table of privacy settings for the VNS.

vnsPrivacyEntry.name: vnsPrivacyEntry
vnsPrivacyEntry.description: Configuration values for a specific privacy setting.

vnsPrivWEPKeyType.name: vnsPrivWEPKeyType
vnsPrivWEPKeyType.description: Type of key in use. none(1) = not cofigured, wepstatic(2) = static WEP, wpapsk(3) = WPA Pre-Shared Key, dynamic(4) = dynamically assigned, wpa(5) = WPA.

vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency.name: vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency
vnsPrivDynamicRekeyFrequency.description: Dynamic WEP re-keying frequency, in seconds. Setting this value to 0 disables rekeying. This value is only meaningful if vnsPrivWEPKeyType = wpapsk(3). For any other values of vnsPrivWEPKeyType, reading or setting this value will return an unsuccessful status and will return a value of null or zero.

vnsPrivWEPKeyLength.name: vnsPrivWEPKeyLength
vnsPrivWEPKeyLength.description: WEP key length, 64, 128, or 152 bits. If vnsPrivWEPKeyType is none, reading or setting this value will return an unsuccessful status and will return a value of null or zero.

vnsPrivUseSharedKey.name: vnsPrivUseSharedKey
vnsPrivUseSharedKey.description: Enables the use of WPA shared key for this VNS.

vnsPrivWPASharedKey.name: vnsPrivWPASharedKey
vnsPrivWPASharedKey.description: The value of the WPA shared key for this VNS. This value is logically WRITE ONLY. Attempts to read this value shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero.

vnsPrivWPA2Enabled.name: vnsPrivWPA2Enabled
vnsPrivWPA2Enabled.description: When true, WPA v.2 support is enabled.

vnsWEPKeyTable.name: vnsWEPKeyTable
vnsWEPKeyTable.description: Table of WEP key entries for a static WEP definition.

vnsWEPKeyEntry.name: vnsWEPKeyEntry
vnsWEPKeyEntry.description: WEP key for a single entry in the table.

vnsWEPKeyIndex.name: vnsWEPKeyIndex
vnsWEPKeyIndex.description: Table index for the WEP key.

vnsWEPKeyValue.name: vnsWEPKeyValue
vnsWEPKeyValue.description: Value of a WEP key for this VNS. This value is logically WRITE ONLY. Attempts to read this value shall return unsuccessful status and values of null or zero.

vns3rdPartyAPTable.name: vns3rdPartyAPTable
vns3rdPartyAPTable.description: Contains a list of 3rd Party access points for the HWC.

vns3rdPartyAPEntry.name: vns3rdPartyAPEntry
vns3rdPartyAPEntry.description: Configuration information for a 3rd party access point.

apMacAddress.name: apMacAddress
apMacAddress.description: Ethernet MAC address of the 3rd party access point.

apIpAddress.name: apIpAddress
apIpAddress.description: IP address of the 3rd party access point.

vnsQoSTable.name: vnsQoSTable
vnsQoSTable.description: This table contains list of per-VNS QoS related configuration.

vnsQoSEntry.name: vnsQoSEntry
vnsQoSEntry.description: An entry related to QoS configuration for the VNS indexed by vnsIfIndex.

vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag
vnsQoSWirelessLegacyFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable legacy QoS feature.

vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag
vnsQoSWirelessWMMFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable WMM feature.

vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag.name: vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag
vnsQoSWireless80211eFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable 802.11e feature.

vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag.name: vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag
vnsQoSWirelessTurboVoiceFlag.description: This variable is used to enable/disable turbo feature.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag.description: Enable/disable the use of DSCP to override Servic Class (SC) value.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideSC.description: Service class (SC) of the override value. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag is enabled.

vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP.name: vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP
vnsQoSPriorityOverrideDSCP.description: DSCP override value to be used for the service class. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSPriorityOverrideFlag is enabled.

vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass.name: vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass
vnsQoSClassificationServiceClass.description: Service Class value for the DSCP code. This field is 64-bytes long. Each byte represents mapping between DSCP and Service Class. Position of each byte in the array represents DSCP code and the content of each byte represents the service class value for that DSCP code. For example, second byte represents DSCP code 1 and its value represents SC value. Value for each byte is equivalent to either of: background = 0, bestEffort = 1, bronze = 2, silver = 3, gold = 4, platinum = 5, premiumVoice = 6, networkControl = 7

vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD.name: vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD
vnsQoSWirelessEnableUAPSD.description: This variable is used to enable/disable U-APSD feature.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVoice.description: If enabled, admission control for voice traffic is used.

vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo.name: vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo
vnsQoSWirelessUseAdmControlVideo.description: If enabled, admission control for vedio traffic is used. This field has a meaning if vnsQoSUseGlobalAdmVoice is enabled.

vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction.name: vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction
vnsQoSWirelessULPolicerAction.description: If doNothing is selected, no action is taken. This is default value. If sendDELTStoClient is selected, AP will send DELTS if a client is abusing in uplink. This field has a meaning only if admission control is enabled for VO or VI.

vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction.name: vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction
vnsQoSWirelessDLPolicerAction.description: If doNothing is selected, no action is taken. This is default value. If downgrade is selected, AP will downgrade all traffic to the highest AC that does not require CAC in downlink. If drop is selected, AP will drop client if it observes a client that is illegally using an AC that has CAC mandatory in downlink. This field has a meaning only if admission control is enabled for VO or VI.

vnsWDSRFTable.name: vnsWDSRFTable
vnsWDSRFTable.description: Contains definitions of the Wireless Distirbution System (WDS) VNS defined on this Controller.

vnsWDSRFEntry.name: vnsWDSRFEntry
vnsWDSRFEntry.description: Configuration elements for a specific WDS VNS.

vnsWDSRFbgService.name: vnsWDSRFbgService
vnsWDSRFbgService.description: Type of service offered by this radio.

vnsWDSRFaService.name: vnsWDSRFaService
vnsWDSRFaService.description: Type of service offered by this radio.

vnsRateControlProfEntry.name: vnsRateControlProfEntry
vnsRateControlProfEntry.description: Name of a specific Rate Control Profile.

vnsRateControlProfInd.name: vnsRateControlProfInd
vnsRateControlProfInd.description: A monotonically increasing integer which acts as index of entries within the named Rate Control Profiles.

vnsRateControlCIR.name: vnsRateControlCIR
vnsRateControlCIR.description: Rate Control Average Rate (CIR) in kbps.

vnsRateControlCBS.name: vnsRateControlCBS
vnsRateControlCBS.description: Rate Control Burst Size (CBS) in bytes.

vnsStatTable.name: vnsStatTable
vnsStatTable.description: The table contains per-VNS specific statistics.

vnsStatEntry.name: vnsStatEntry
vnsStatEntry.description: An entry in vnsStatTable. Each entry is indexed by VNS ID

vnsStatRadiusTotRequests.name: vnsStatRadiusTotRequests
vnsStatRadiusTotRequests.description: Total requests sent to radius server.

vnsStatRadiusReqFailed.name: vnsStatRadiusReqFailed
vnsStatRadiusReqFailed.description: Requests that failed to be processed by radius server.

vnsStatRadiusReqRejected.name: vnsStatRadiusReqRejected
vnsStatRadiusReqRejected.description: Requests that have been rejected by radius server.

vnsExceptionStatTable.name: vnsExceptionStatTable
vnsExceptionStatTable.description: The table contains list of per-VNS exception-filters specific statistics.

vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied.name: vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied
vnsExceptionStatPktsDenied.description: Total packets that are denied by defined filters.

vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed.name: vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed
vnsExceptionStatPktsAllowed.description: Total packets that are allowed by defined filters.

vnsWDSStatTable.name: vnsWDSStatTable
vnsWDSStatTable.description: Contains statistics of the Wireless Distirbution System (WDS) VNSes defined on this Controller.

vnsWDSStatEntry.name: vnsWDSStatEntry
vnsWDSStatEntry.description: Statistics elements for a specific WDS VNS.

vnsWDSStatAPRole.name: vnsWDSStatAPRole
vnsWDSStatAPRole.description: Role of the AP in WDS tree. All the statistics and configuration information in this table has no meaning if the role is unknown(-1).

vnsWDSStatAPRadio.name: vnsWDSStatAPRadio
vnsWDSStatAPRadio.description: Radio and freq on which uplink WDS is established, N/A if connected over etherent (value are 'a:<freq>', 'b/g:<freq>', or 'N/A')

vnsWDSStatAPParent.name: vnsWDSStatAPParent
vnsWDSStatAPParent.description: AP Name of the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatSSID.name: vnsWDSStatSSID
vnsWDSStatSSID.description: SSID of the WDS VNS where parent WDS link is established.

vnsWDSStatRxFrame.name: vnsWDSStatRxFrame
vnsWDSStatRxFrame.description: Received frames from the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatTxFrame.name: vnsWDSStatTxFrame
vnsWDSStatTxFrame.description: Transmitted frames to the parent AP.

vnsWDSStatRxError.name: vnsWDSStatRxError
